				<h1>Participant Information</h1>
				<p>
					I would like to invite you to take part in my research project. Before
					you decide, I would like you to understand why the research is being
					conducted and what it would involve for you. Talk to others about the
					study if you wish. Please ask me if anything is unclear.
				</p>
				<h3>What is the purpose of the project?</h3>
				<p>
					Over the past few months I have been developing a web app which takes
					drawn lines on paper and converts them into music. The idea is that
					this is a more intuitive or accessible way to notate music than other
					traditional forms. At this stage, an evaluation is needed to determine
					if the app fulfils its goals.
				</p>
				<h3>Your role in the study.</h3>
				<p>
					The study consists of three sections: A pre-interview, testing, and a
					post-interview.
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>
						The pre interview should be around 10 minutes long and will be used
						to gauge your level of musical experience.
					</li>
					<li>
						For testing I will ask you to use the app for 10-20 minutes over 5
						days. It is not necessary for those days to be consecutive. I will
						give you some prompts to follow so that you engage with the app in
						several ways.
					</li>
					<li>
						The post interview will be under an hour and will be used to gain
						insight into how you used the app, what works and what doesn't etc.
					</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					The interview times are indicative, but I will try to keep them close
					to the stated times. I hope for the post interview to be completed by
					Sunday the 1st of May.
				</p>
				<h3>Why have you been invited to participate?</h3>
				<p>
					I'm looking for a group of 6 to 10 participants with varying levels of
					music experience. I have picked you out because I think you will add a
					valuable contribution to my study!
				</p>
				<h3>Do you have to take part?</h3>
				<p>
					No! It is entirely voluntary, and I will hold no grudge against you if
					you decide not to participate. The study will be made very clear to
					you before you participate and I will answer any questions you might
					have. If you agree to take part, I will ask you to sign a consent
					form. You are free to withdraw at any time without giving a reason.
				</p>
				<h3>
					What are the possible disadvantages and risks involved in taking part?
				</h3>
				<p>There are no disadvantages that I can think of!</p>
				<h3>What are the possible benefits of taking part?</h3>
